In summary, our breakdown of each part includes:

- Part A (for loop): Iterations: The linear search involves finding each element in the array using a binary search, which takes constant time (log2 N) to perform. We also want to mention that this analysis can be improved further by exploring more complex operations, such as partial sorting or median of medians algorithms.
